ANTHRAX - RUSSIA (06): (ALTAI) HUMAN, BOVINE
********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

[1]
Date: Thu 30 Aug 2012
Source: Nakanune.RU [in Russian, machine trans., edited]
http://www.nakanune.ru/news/2012/8/30/22284600


There are 5 patients diagnosed with anthrax at the Biysk hospital. As the Altai Territory Rospotrebnadzor [Federal Service for Consumer Protection and Human Welfare] reported to Nakanune.RU news, the diagnosis was confirmed by laboratory tests in 4 cases.

Druzhba village residents, who were in close contact with sick and dead animals, received prophylactic treatment, and 8 people were targeted for preventive medical monitoring and hospitalized in the infectious ward.

Specialists from Altai Territory Rospotrebnadzor, together with specialists of the local Healthcare and Pharmaceutical Industry Department continue to implement preventive and anti-epidemic measures, including door-to-door visits, medical supervision of villagers, and disinfection measures in the villages of Druzhba and Marushka in Tselinny district. According to the results of medical monitoring, patients in these villages have been identified, and provided with the required medicines and disinfectants.

A total of 67 cattle breeders have been vaccinated, village assemblies have been conducted, and the population has been informed about preventive measures.

Veterinary specialists of the Altai region will deliver a package of measures to prevent the spread of the disease among animals.

--
